title: Daubarai, Kėdainiai
text: Daubarai (formerly , ) is a village in <a href="K%C4%97dainiai%20district%20municipality">Kėdainiai district municipality</a>, in <a href="Kaunas%20County">Kaunas County</a>, in central <a href="Lithuania">Lithuania</a>. According to the 2011 census, the village had a population of 5 people. It is located from <a href="Skaistgiriai%2C%20K%C4%97dainiai">Skaistgiriai</a>, by the Kriausupys rivulet, alongside the road <a href="Kampai%20II">Kampai II</a>-<a href="Pernarava">Pernarava</a>.
